<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585736>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Abyssorchomene chevreuxi (Stebbing, 1906), habitus and LM from syntype female ‘A’, MNHN, from Princesse Alice stn 1534; A1, A2, mouthparts, G1, G2, P5, P7 from syntype female ‘B’, all after C. De Broyer (unpublished); male A2, U2, U3, T, male from eastern North Atlantic Ocean (48°50.02'N 16°30.42'W), 4842 m. Scale bars: unknown for De Broyer material; remainder, 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5585736/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

